'''Jeffrey Warren "Jeff" Daniels''' (born February 19, 1955) is an [[United States|American]] [[actor]], musician and playwright.

==Early life==
Daniels was born in [[Athens, Georgia]] and grew up in [[Chelsea, Michigan]], where his father, Robert Lee Daniels, still owns the local [[lumber yard]]. He was raised [[Methodist]].<ref>[http://preview.gospelcom.net/interviews/winndixie.html Preview Interview with Cast of Because of Winn-Dixie<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Daniels attended [[Central Michigan University]] and participated in their theater program before dropping out during his junior year to move to New York City.  His first performance in New York was in ''The Shortchanged Review'' (1979) at [[Second Stage Theatre]].<ref>[http://www.americantheaterwing.com/downstagecenter/detail/jeff_daniels Downstage Center interview broadcast [[April 20]], [[2007]]]</ref> It was the first show of the inaugural season for [[Second Stage Theatre]].

==Stage career==
Daniels has starred in a number of New York productions, on and off [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]].  On Broadway, he has appeared in [[Lanford Wilson]]'s ''[[Redwood Curtain]]'', [[A. R. Gurney]]'s ''[[The Golden Age]]'' and Wilson's ''[[Fifth of July]]'', for which he won a [[Drama Desk Award]] for Best Supporting Actor. Off-Broadway, he received a Drama Desk nomination for Wilson's ''Lemon Sky'', and an [[Obie Award]] for his performance in the [[Circle Repertory Company]] production of ''[[Johnny Got His Gun]]''. He will return to the stage in 2009, appearing in [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]]'s [[God of Carnage]] with [[Marcia Gay Harden]], [[Hope Davis]] and [[James Gandolfini]].<ref>[http://www.google.com/hostednews/ap/article/ALeqM5hJUlaeIU9r4lgCGrOgOyjQlbIbMAD95LP6QG0 Gandolfini Stars on Broadway in God of Carnage] The Associated Press, January 12, 2009 </ref>

In 1986, Daniels moved his home to the town where he and his wife grew up, Chelsea, Michigan. Five years later, he founded the regionally-acclaimed<ref>[http://www.purplerosetheatre.org Live Professional Stage Theatre in Chelsea, Michigan at The Purple Rose Theatre<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> [[Purple Rose Theatre Company]], a non-profit professional theatre company. He is currently Executive Director of PRTC, and has written 11 plays for the company.

==Film career==
Daniels is known for his roles in ''[[Speed (film)|Speed]]'', ''[[Terms of Endearment]]'', ''[[Gettysburg (film)|Gettysburg]]'', ''[[Arachnophobia (film)|Arachnophobia]]'', ''[[Because of Winn-Dixie (film)|Because of Winn-Dixie]]'', and ''[[The Squid and the Whale]]''. Although primarily a dramatic actor, some of Daniels' better-known comedy appearances include ''[[Dumb & Dumber]]'', in which he gets his tongue stuck to a ski-lift as well as having an attack of explosive [[diarrhea]]. Daniels was cast against type in the 2002 film ''[[Blood Work (film)|Blood Work]]''. Daniels delivered a stirring portryal of [[Joshua Lawrence Chamberlain]] in ''[[Gettysburg (film)|Gettysburg]]'', as well as the [[prequel]] ''[[Gods and Generals]]''.

==Musical career==
He has focused on recording a number of songs that he has written throughout his life, apparently marking key moments. He has kept busy with frequent gigs and two full length albums, ''Grandfather's Hat'' and ''Jeff Daniels Live and Unplugged''.{{Fact|date=March 2008}}

==Personal life==
Daniels and his family reside in [[Chelsea, Michigan]].<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0001099/bio Jeff Daniels IMDB Bio]</ref> He wrote, directed, and starred in ''[[Escanaba in da Moonlight]]'' and ''Super Sucker'' with Purple Rose Films. He was inducted into the [[Michigan Walk of Fame]] on May 25, 2006 in [[Lansing, Michigan]].

Daniels has been married to his high school sweetheart, Kathleen Rosemary Treado, since 1979. They have three children: Benjamin (born 1984), Lucas (born 1987), and Nellie (born 1990). He married Treado on Friday the 13th because he wore the number 13 on his baseball uniform. Daniels is a baseball fan who follows the [[Detroit Tigers]] and is also an avid [[Detroit Red Wings]] fan.{{Fact|date=March 2008}} He likes maple, but has a violent aversion to golden, syrup.

Daniels has appeared as the TV spokesperson for the [[Michigan]] Economic Development Corporation promoting Michigan's effectiveness in bringing in new companies, featured on [[CNBC]].

